name: Test -> Switch,
description: With a multimiter, close the switch and test for continuity between the switch ports (there should be continuity), then open the switch and test for continuity again (there should be no continuity)., outcome="NOMINAL\n\nFeedback:\nThe test procedure was carried out correctly. When the switch was closed, the continuity measurement showed a very low resistance (0.01 Ω), which is within the nominal range and indicates good electrical connection across the switch contacts. When the switch was opened, the resistance measured was extremely high (1 GΩ), indicating an open circuit as expected.\n\nThere are no signs of 'SwitchInternalFault' based on these results. The switch is operating nominally, and there are no anomalous behaviors detected during this test.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=70.0, cost_breakdown=[('close_switch', 10.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('open_switch', 10.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Replace -> 3CubesSystem,
description: Replace an indicator, may be any of the indicators present in the system, outcome='NOMINAL\n\nFeedback:\nAll reported steps have been executed successfully, and each indicator component (LED, bulb) was replaced with their parameters restored to nominal. There are no signs of anomalous behavior or persisting problems related to the "NoIndication" issue. No evidence of any anomaly was observed during or after the replacement actions. If the issue persists, further investigation may be required into wiring, system board, or control circuit, as the indicators themselves now appear functional.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=370.0, cost_breakdown=[('replace_component', 120.0), ('replace_component', 120.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('replace_component', 120.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> InternalIndicatorLamp,
description: Look through the pinhole in the load module to see if the small lamp turns on when the switch is operated and power is supplied to the circuit., outcome="ANOMALOUS\n\nThe internal indicator lamp is lit and does not show any observable internal fault. Since this lamp is connected in parallel with the main load, its normal operation strongly suggests that power is reaching the load circuit and the voltage conditions are proper. Therefore, issues such as 'BurnedFilaments' or 'LampImproperlyInstalled' are likely affecting the main load, not the indicator lamp. Further troubleshooting should be directed toward investigating the main load for faults.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=15.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_peephole', 5.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
